akespeare historians argued whether or not a particular sonnet was actually written by Shakespeare. Both sides used grammatical and vocabulary as evidence; as well as trying to infer where it was written based upon the imagery and dialect/syntactic structure that was used. Another example would be plagiarism and trademark, where people use linguistical patterns like syntax and sentence structure to determine if a particular text or idea is too similar to another's text or patent.%0a%3c %0a%3c https://lama.hypotheses.org/70%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
